<paragraph blockId="22.[452,1136,265,291]" box="[452,1136,265,291]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">
Subfamily 
<taxonomicName authority="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm, 1889" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" box="[581,1136,265,291]" family="Muscidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Reinwardtiinae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[581,775,265,291]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Reinwardtiinae</emphasis>
Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm, 1889
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="117" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1399,330,427]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">
This taxon is a heterogeneous, para- or polyphyletic assemblage of genera which is also reflected in its diverse costal chaetotaxy. Species from seven among the 15 currently recognized genera (
<tableCitation box="[1236,1323,366,392]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="5.[189,258,265,291]" captionTargetBox="[238,1379,394,1980]" captionText="Table 1 (continued on next 4 pages). Summary of vein C chaetotaxy with respect to multistate characterA for genus-group taxa of Fanniidae Schnabel &amp; Dziedcicki, 1911 and Muscidae Latreille, 1802. Examined genera highlighted in yellow. See ‘Material and methods’ for explanation of character states A0–8." pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Table 1</tableCitation>
) were examined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1398,474,535]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis box="[189,199,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Robineau-Desvoidy, 1830" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[221,637,474,500]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Muscina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[221,322,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Muscina</emphasis>
Robineau-Desvoidy, 1830
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[653,762,474,500]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1876,1902]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,677,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[189,1399,670,1856]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 12. ♀♀ of Muscidae Latreille, 1802. A. Muscina stabulans (Fallén, 1823), detail of wing showing CS1‒3, dorsal view. B. Palpibracus trivittatus (Malloch, 1934), detail of wing showing CS1‒3, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784155/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Rodhain &amp; Villeneuve, 1915" authorityName="Rodhain &amp; Villeneuve" authorityYear="1915" box="[784,1277,474,501]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Passeromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[784,934,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Passeromyia</emphasis>
Rodhain &amp; Villeneuve, 1915
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Meinert, 1890" authorityName="Meinert" authorityYear="1890" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Philornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1289,1398,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Philornis</emphasis>
Meinert, 1890
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[188,1399,555,653]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">
The examined species belonging to the above genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1889" box="[841,1020,555,581]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Reinwardtiinae">Reinwardtiinae</taxonomicName>
share the prevalent muscid state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[188,224,590,616]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">
A 
<quantity box="[210,224,590,616]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" unit="in" value="4.0">4</quantity>
</emphasis>
in which vein C is bare dorsally and extensively setulose ventrally: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1830" box="[1040,1141,592,617]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Muscina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1040,1141,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Muscina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5 spp), 
<taxonomicName authority="Villeneuve, 1915" authorityName="Villeneuve" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Passeromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heterochaeta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Passeromyia heterochaeta</emphasis>
Villeneuve, 1915
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Pont, 1970" authorityName="Pont" authorityYear="1970" box="[606,835,626,652]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Passeromyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="steini">
<emphasis box="[606,698,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">P. steini</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pont A. C. &amp; Shinonaga S." box="[705,835,626,652]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" pagination="193 - 199" refId="ref15633" refString="Pont A. C. &amp; Shinonaga S. 1970. A new genus of Muscidae from Palaearctic East Asia (Diptera, Muscidae). Japanese Journal of Sanitary Zoology 21: 193 - 199." type="journal article" year="1970">Pont, 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meinert" authorityYear="1890" box="[847,956,626,652]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Philornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[847,956,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Philornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5 spp).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784153" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6784153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784153/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" startId="22.[189,232,1930,1956]" targetBox="[189,1398,704,1908]" targetPageId="22">
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1398,1930,1991]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,284,1930,1956]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Fig. 11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Schiner, 1868" authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" box="[294,729,1930,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Atherigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[294,549,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">Atherigona orientalis</emphasis>
Schiner, 1868
</taxonomicName>
, ♀. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[785,806,1930,1956]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">A</emphasis>
. Wing, ventral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1073,1093,1930,1956]" pageId="22" pageNumber="116">B</emphasis>
. Detail of wing showing CS1‒3, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,738,265,292]" box="[189,738,265,292]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis box="[189,199,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm, 1893" authorityName="Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm" authorityYear="1893" box="[214,738,265,292]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Synthesiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,383,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Synthesiomyia</emphasis>
Brauer &amp; Bergenstamm, 1893
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[188,1399,311,408]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
The only included species, 
<taxonomicName box="[503,770,311,337]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Synthesiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudipes">
<emphasis box="[503,770,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Synthesiomyia nudipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has vein C only fully setulose ventrally on CS2 (state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[188,223,346,372]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">A2</emphasis>
), although some irregular ventral costal setulae extent onto CS2 or (females only) even the basal part of CS3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1364,440,467]" box="[189,1364,440,467]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis box="[189,199,441,466]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart, 1851" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1851" box="[214,605,440,467]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Brachygasterina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,410,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Brachygasterina</emphasis>
Macquart, 1851
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1863" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1863" box="[617,941,440,466]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Palpibracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[617,760,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Palpibracus</emphasis>
Rondani, 1863
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[957,1061,440,466]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1876,1902]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,677,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[189,1399,670,1856]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 12. ♀♀ of Muscidae Latreille, 1802. A. Muscina stabulans (Fallén, 1823), detail of wing showing CS1‒3, dorsal view. B. Palpibracus trivittatus (Malloch, 1934), detail of wing showing CS1‒3, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784155/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Stein, 1911" authorityName="Stein" authorityYear="1911" box="[1085,1364,440,466]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Psilochaeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1085,1224,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Psilochaeta</emphasis>
Stein, 1911
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,486,654]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
The examined species of these three exclusively South American genera differ substantially from the preceding reinwardtiine genera by the dorsally extensively setulose vein C (state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1221,1257,521,547]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">A8</emphasis>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1275,1385,521,548]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1876,1902]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,677,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-150@24.[189,1399,670,1856]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 12. ♀♀ of Muscidae Latreille, 1802. A. Muscina stabulans (Fallén, 1823), detail of wing showing CS1‒3, dorsal view. B. Palpibracus trivittatus (Malloch, 1934), detail of wing showing CS1‒3, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6784155" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6784155/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="(Malloch, 1922)" baseAuthorityName="Malloch" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[189,792,557,583]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Brachygasterina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvohumeralis">
<emphasis box="[189,576,557,583]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Brachygasterina fulvohumeralis</emphasis>
(Malloch, 1922)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart, 1851" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1851" box="[811,1235,557,584]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Brachygasterina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violaceiventris">
<emphasis box="[811,1025,557,583]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">B. violaceiventris</emphasis>
Macquart, 1851
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1863" box="[1255,1398,557,583]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Palpibracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1255,1398,557,583]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Palpibracus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(12 spp) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wiedemann, 1830)" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[351,856,592,618]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Psilochaeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalybea">
<emphasis box="[351,606,592,618]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Psilochaeta chalybea</emphasis>
(Wiedemann, 1830)
</taxonomicName>
. Only 
<taxonomicName authority="Malloch, 1934" authorityName="Malloch" authorityYear="1934" box="[939,1399,592,618]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Brachygasterina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis box="[939,1214,592,618]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Brachygasterina major</emphasis>
Malloch, 1934
</taxonomicName>
differs by having the dorsal setulae restricted to CS2 and CS3 (females) or CS3 (males) (state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1292,1327,627,653]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">A7</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
